Simple example TBX application to show hooking events to
toolbox gadgets.

Running the application puts an icon on the iconbar.

The iconbar menu gives two options.
- show the application information
- quit the application.

Clicking select on the iconbar shows the "Reverse text" window.

This window consists of:
- a writeable field for you to enter some text in.
- a display field that will show the number of characters
  currently in the writeable field.
- a "Reverse text" button that will reverse the text in the
  writeable field.

